@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>This application is a digital archive and management system for musical scores and sheet music. 
   It is designed for personal use as well as for wider collaboration within music ensembles, choirs, orchestras, or cultural associations.
</p>

<p>
The system enables users to upload, organize, search, and manage sheet music in a structured and efficient way. 
Scores can be categorized by multiple attributes, including composer, title, musical genre, performer, and date. 
Users can perform both category-based searches and full-archive searches to quickly find specific compositions or different versions of the same score.</p>

<p>Each user has a personal account secured with a username and password. 
Registered users can add new scores, browse the archive, create a list of favorite scores, and download or export files for local use or printing. 
To maintain data integrity, users are only allowed to delete scores that they personally uploaded and the administrators.</p>

<p>The goal of the application is to simplify the organization and accessibility of musical materials while supporting collaboration and long-term digital preservation of sheet music collections.</p>